SIMPLE: sooty
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sooty
<hw>Soot"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Sootier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Sootiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>s<?/tig</ets>. See
<er>Soot</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to soot;
producing soot; soiled by soot.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Fire of <xex>sooty</xex>
coal.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a dark brown or black color like soot;
fuliginous; dusky; dark.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The grisly legions that troop
under the <xex>sooty</xex> flag of Acheron.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sooty albatross</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>an
albatross (<spn>Phoebetria fuliginosa</spn>) found chiefly in the
Pacific Ocean; -- called also <altname>nellie</altname>.</cd> --
<col><b>Sooty tern</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a tern (<spn>Sterna
fuliginosa</spn>) found chiefly in tropical seas.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sooty</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sooty
<hw>Soot"y</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To black or foul with soot.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sootied</qex> with noisome smoke.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sop</ent>⟦br⟧
